  ('CISA-00337', 1, 'Hard', 'Risk-Based Audit Approach', 'An IS auditor is developing an audit plan for a financial institution. The institution recently implemented a new core banking system. Which of the following factors would MOST significantly influence the auditor''s decision to prioritize the audit of the new core banking system?', 'The project was completed on time and within budget.', 'The vendor has a strong reputation and a long history of successful implementations.', 'The core banking system processes a high volume of critical financial transactions.', 'The system has built-in automated controls to prevent fraud and errors.', 'C', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (C): The core banking system processes a high volume of critical financial transactions.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: The project was c