  ('CISA-00387', 5, 'Medium', 'Data Classification', 'During a review of data classification practices, an auditor finds that a company has implemented a classification scheme but employees are not consistently applying it. Which of the following actions is the MOST important for the auditor to recommend?', 'Implement automated data classification tools.', 'Develop and deliver training on the data classification scheme and its application.', 'Revise the data classification scheme to be simpler.', 'Increase the frequency of internal security audits.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Develop and deliver training on the data classification scheme and its application.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Implement automated data classification tools. → This approach either ignores the issue, escalates prematur