Y THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Implement biometric access control for the backup generator room. → This approach either ignores the issue, escalates prematurely without documentation, or follows an unstructured process that creates audit gaps. Auditors must always follow structured procedures.  Option B: Relocate the backup generator inside the data center perimeter. → This option misses the audit objective or applies the wrong standard. Audit procedures must be aligned with scope and audit standards (ISACA, COBIT).  Option D: Reduce the sensitivity of data processed during backup generator operation. → This might be a procedural step but not the complete or correct response. Context matters in audit decisions.'),
  ('CISA-00389', 2, 'Hard', 'IT Governance Frameworks and Compliance', 'During a CISA review of a multinational corporation''s IT governance structure, the auditor discovers that the organization uses a hybrid IT governance model. While most business units adhere to a centralized IT strategy and risk management framework mandated by headquarters, a recently acquired subsidiary in a highly regulated industry maintains a decentralized model with its own distinct IT strategy and risk appetite. The subsidiary argues that its specialized operations and stringent regulatory requirements necessitate this autonomy. Which of the following actions should the CISA MOST likely take FIRST?', 'Review the legal and regulatory requirements specific to the subsidiary''s industry and geographic location to determine if the decentralized model is justified and compliant.', 'Immediately report the deviation from the centralized IT strategy to senior management and recommend a complete integration of the subsidiary into the corporate IT governance framework.', 'Assess the potential for cost savings and efficiency gains by mandating the adoption of the centralized IT strategy across the entire organization, regardless of regulatory requirements.', 'Benchmark the subsidiary''s IT performance against competitors using similar decentralized models to determine if it is operating efficiently and effectively.', 'A', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (A): Review the legal and regulatory requirements specific to the subsidiary''s industry and geographic location to determine if the decentralized model is justified and compliant.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial 