  ('CISA-00410', 5, 'Medium', 'Data Classification', 'During an audit of a government agency, the auditor finds that a large amount of sensitive data is stored on shared network drives without proper classification labels. This makes it difficult to identify and protect the data appropriately. What should the auditor FIRST recommend?', 'Implement a data encryption solution for all data stored on the shared drives.', 'Establish a formal data classification policy and process, including roles, responsibilities, and training.', 'Restrict access to the shared network drives to only authorized personnel.', 'Conduct a data mining exercise to identify and automatically classify all sensitive data.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Establish a formal data classification policy and process, including roles, responsibilities, and training.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up