e finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option B: The IT strategic plan is too detailed and prescriptive for the organization''s needs. → This approach either ignores the issue, escalates prematurely without documentation, or follows an unstructured process that creates audit gaps. Auditors must always follow structured procedures.  Option C: The IT strategic plan should be separate from the overall business goals to maintain IT''s independence. → This option misses the audit objective or applies the wrong standard. Audit procedures must be aligned with scope and audit standards (ISACA, COBIT).  Option D: The inclusion of measurable objectives and KPIs is not necessary if IT is adequately staffed and funded. → This might be a procedural step but not the complete or correct response. Context matters in audit decisions.'),
  ('CISA-00443', 2, 'Medium', 'IT Resource Management', 'During a review of IT resource management, an IS auditor discovers that the IT department does not have a formal capacity planning process. Server utilization is consistently high, leading to performance issues during peak hours. Which of the following actions should the IS auditor recommend FIRST?', 'Implement a chargeback system to allocate IT costs to business units.', 'Develop and implement a formal capacity planning process to anticipate future resource needs.', 'Increase the IT budget to purchase additional server hardware.', 'Outsource all IT operations to a third-party provider.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Develop and implement a formal capacity planning process to anticipate future resource needs.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: I