  ('CISA-00468', 1, 'Medium', 'Audit Evidence', 'While performing a review of user access controls for a critical application, an IS auditor observes that several users have elevated privileges beyond what their job descriptions require. The BEST course of action for the IS auditor is to:', 'Immediately revoke the unnecessary privileges.', 'Inform the users that their privileges are excessive.', 'Document the finding and include it in the audit report.', 'Investigate the approval process for granting elevated privileges.', 'D', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (D): Investigate the approval process for granting elevated privileges.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: Immediately revoke the unnecessary privileges. → This approach either ignores the issue, escalates prematurely without documentation, or follows an unst