  ('CISA-00533', 3, 'Medium', 'System Integration', 'An organization is integrating a new CRM system with its existing ERP system. The IS auditor is concerned about the security implications of the integration, particularly regarding data access and authorization. What should the IS auditor recommend as the MOST important control to review?', 'The physical security of the servers hosting the integrated systems.', 'The data retention policies for both the CRM and ERP systems.', 'The access control mechanisms and authorization protocols used for data exchange between the systems.', 'The disaster recovery plan for the CRM system only.', 'C', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (C): The access control mechanisms and authorization protocols used for data exchange between the systems.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why They''re Wrong:  Option A: The 