  ('CISA-00534', 1, 'Medium', 'Audit Planning', 'During the planning phase of an audit of a recently implemented cloud-based CRM system, the IS auditor discovers that the organization lacks a formal security incident response plan that specifically addresses cloud environments. Which of the following is the MOST appropriate action for the IS auditor to take?', 'Expand the audit scope to include the development of a cloud-specific security incident response plan.', 'Document the finding in the audit report and adjust the audit procedures to assess the existing security controls around incident detection and logging.', 'Immediately recommend that management suspend use of the cloud-based CRM system until a suitable incident response plan is in place.', 'Reduce the audit scope to exclude areas not covered by existing incident response procedures.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Document the finding in the audit report and adjust the audit procedures to assess the existing security controls around incident detection and logging.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as imp