  ('CISA-00548', 1, 'Hard', 'Audit Planning and Risk Assessment', 'What should the auditor FIRST recommend during the risk assessment phase?', 'Implement additional hardware resources, such as increased processing power and memory, to improve system performance during peak hours.', 'Conduct a performance test on the transaction monitoring system using simulated peak transaction volumes to identify the specific bottlenecks.', 'Review the service level agreements (SLAs) with third-party vendors providing data feeds and system components to ensure they meet the bank''s performance requirements.', 'Prioritize a review of the data transformation logic and algorithms within the transaction monitoring system to identify inefficient or redundant processes.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Conduct a performance test on the transaction monitoring system using simulated peak transaction volumes to identify the specific bottlenecks.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear acc