  ('CISA-00549', 1, 'Hard', 'Audit Planning and Risk Assessment', 'What is the MOST important action for the auditor to take during the audit planning phase to assess the risk associated with these social engineering attacks?', 'Review the incident response plan to ensure it includes procedures for handling phishing attacks and compromised user accounts.', 'Conduct unannounced simulated phishing campaigns targeting employees to evaluate the effectiveness of the security awareness program and identify vulnerable users.', 'Assess the configuration of the MFA system to ensure it is properly implemented and enforced for all users and applications.', 'Analyze the network traffic logs to identify patterns and sources of phishing emails entering the organization''s network.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Conduct unannounced simulated phishing campaigns targeting employees to evaluate the effectiveness of the security awareness program and identify vulnerable users.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management und