  ('CISA-00584', 1, 'Hard', 'Audit Procedures and Techniques', 'Which audit technique would provide the auditor with the BEST evidence of the POS system''s failover capability?', 'Reviewing the network infrastructure diagrams and design specifications to verify the redundancy configuration.', 'Observing the IT staff''s procedures for monitoring network performance and responding to service disruptions.', 'Conducting a simulated network outage and observing the system''s automated failover process to the redundant connection.', 'Examining the historical logs of network events to identify past instances of failover and their associated outcomes.', 'C', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (C): Conducting a simulated network outage and observing the system''s automated failover process to the redundant connection.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compliance purposes • Basis for future follow-up audits  ❌ INCORRECT OPTIONS - Why