  ('CISA-00588', 1, 'Hard', 'Audit Procedures and Techniques', 'What is the GREATEST risk associated with migrating the existing firewall rules to the new system, and what should the auditor recommend FIRST?', 'Incompatibility with the new firewall architecture; recommend performing a compatibility test of the rule set.', 'Introduction of new security vulnerabilities due to outdated rules; recommend a comprehensive review and cleanup of the existing rule set before migration.', 'Performance degradation of the new firewall; recommend optimizing the rule set after migration.', 'Disruption of network connectivity during migration; recommend performing the migration during off-peak hours.', 'B', '✅ CORRECT ANSWER (B): Introduction of new security vulnerabilities due to outdated rules; recommend a comprehensive review and cleanup of the existing rule set before migration.  COMPREHENSIVE EXPLANATION: This answer reflects best practices in IT audit methodology. The auditor must follow a structured approach when identifying control weaknesses or compliance issues. Proper documentation and escalation ensure that findings are recorded accurately and stakeholders can take corrective action within appropriate timeframes.  REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: A large financial institution undergoes an audit of their payment processing system. The auditor identifies that critical reconciliation controls are manual and lack proper segregation of duties. Instead of just noting the issue, the auditor formally documents the finding, rates its severity (High - potential for fraud), and recommends implementation of automated controls with proper authorization workflows. This structured approach ensures management acknowledges the risk and allocates resources for remediation.  WHY THIS MATTERS: In audit work, how you communicate findings is as important as what you find. Proper reporting ensures: • Management understands the business impact • Clear accountability for remediation • Audit trail for compli